going out with a new release.

00:02:06.890 --> 00:02:10.009
And we have new
testing track features

00:02:10.009 --> 00:02:11.360
that help to reduce that risk.

00:02:11.360 --> 00:02:14.810
And so you can now
use Play Publishing

00:02:14.810 --> 00:02:18.815
for testing and
sending out the APK

00:02:18.815 --> 00:02:22.550
to up to 100 internal
dog food testers.

00:02:22.550 --> 00:02:24.330
So that's the internal
testing track.

00:02:24.330 --> 00:02:29.030
We also now have multiple
testing tracks for close betas.

00:02:29.030 --> 00:02:33.320
And then, also to help you
reduce the bugs in your apps

00:02:33.320 --> 00:02:35.600
and improve that
quality, there's

00:02:35.600 --> 00:02:37.850
some new features
in Android Vitals

00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:40.260
and new features in
the pre-launch report.

00:02:40.260 --> 00:02:44.600
In Vitals, we have new
metrics, like app startup time.

00:02:44.600 --> 00:02:47.630
We've also launched a new
overview page in Vitals

00:02:47.630 --> 00:02:50.610
that draws your
attention to anomalies.

00:02:50.610 --> 00:02:54.560
If some of the Vitals
metrics are particularly bad,

00:02:54.560 --> 00:02:56.195
then it'll highlight
those to you

00:02:56.195 --> 00:02:58.820
so you know which
ones to prioritize.

00:02:58.820 --> 00:03:00.620
With the pre-launch
report-- so that

00:03:00.620 --> 00:03:05.330
is the automated crawler
that tests apps prior to them

00:03:05.330 --> 00:03:06.830
going into production.

00:03:06.830 --> 00:03:09.440
And we've launched
some new features today

00:03:09.440 --> 00:03:13.390
that enable you to reach further
into the corners of your app

00:03:13.390 --> 00:03:16.250
that the crawler might not
have otherwise reached.

00:03:16.250 --> 00:03:21.590
Features like, a developer
can record scripts

00:03:21.590 --> 00:03:24.920
in Android Studio that
help the crawler to go

00:03:24.920 --> 00:03:26.780
into particular
parts of the app.

00:03:26.780 --> 00:03:30.260
Game developers,
if you use Open GL,

00:03:30.260 --> 00:03:33.590
you can create demo loops that
help the pre-launch report

00:03:33.590 --> 00:03:36.960
crawler to reach different
parts of your app as well.

00:03:36.960 --> 00:03:38.870
And so all these
features will mean

00:03:38.870 --> 00:03:40.740
that once your app
hits production,

00:03:40.740 --> 00:03:44.180
it's been much more scrutinized,
eliminating more of these bugs.

